# Onboarding & Profile Ecosystem — Refined Architecture

## 1. Core Architecture & Reusability

**Decision: Onboarding is part of a unified Profile Ecosystem, not an isolated wizard.**

The logic and UI components built for this onboarding flow must be reusable. While the first-time onboarding will use a full-page, immersive layout, the underlying components (Interest selector, Searchable City input, Profile Completion Calculator) will be architected to easily plug into the standard Profile Edit page later.

*   **Shared Logic**: The `ProfileCompletionPercentage` calculation and "Points Awarding" logic will exist centrally (e.g., in the `User` model and a shared service or utility method), ensuring that if a user skips onboarding but later completes their profile via the Edit page, they still get the 50 points.
*   **Existing Users Strategy**: Existing users will **not** be forced into the onboarding wizard. A data migration/update script will set `IsOnboardingCompleted = true` for all existing users. They will naturally interact with the profile completion system via soft nudges on the dashboard and profile pages, using the same completion percentage logic.

