## 2. Updated Data Model & Completion Formula

### Volunteering Interests
We will add a new `Interests` field to the `User` model to capture the user's preferred volunteering sectors. This is critical for future recommendation algorithms and personalization.

### Profile Completion Percentage Formula
The formula is updated to balance the newly added `Interests` field:

| Field | Weight | Rule |
|---|---|---|
| City | 15% | Not null/empty |
| Interests | 15% | ≥ 1 interest selected |
| Bio | 30% | ≥ 20 characters |
| Skills | 25% | ≥ 1 skill entered |
| Experience | 15% | ≥ 15 characters |
| **Total** | **100%** | |

```csharp
// On User model (computed, not persisted)
[NotMapped]
public int ProfileCompletionPercentage
{
    get
    {
        int score = 0;
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(City)) score += 15;
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(Interests)) score += 15;
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(Bio) && Bio.Trim().Length >= 20) score += 30;
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(Skills) && Skills.Split(',', StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries).Length >= 1) score += 25;
        if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(Experience) && Experience.Trim().Length >= 15) score += 15;
        return score;
    }
}
```

